<br>
My standard dungeon gear gives me 1749 hp, 2613mana, and 860 ac self bufed.  Most of the time I find my self sitting near full mana since I use it spareingly.  The other night in sebelis on a corpse recovery, we had a ten minuet fight when the cleric managed to agro like ten frogs on another goup and us.  By the end of the fight I was out of mana and meding just to get a heal off in time to keep someone barely alive.  It's times like this when the larger mana pool comes into factor, not when you're group is going smooth.  If I had had any less mana, someone would have died.<br>
<br>
In the general coruse of a xp crawl, your mana pool size doesn't matter.  When things go wrong, it very much does matter. <p>Batou Thornhill<BR>
Preserver of the 55th Season<BR>
Harbingers<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urandomuser.showPublicProfile?language=EN>random user</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/20/01 11:24:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re: wis</span><hr size=1> In re 200 wis as everyone has said it's just the cap, mana pool is more important than magically hitting 200.<br>
<br>
In regards to higher wis helping not fizzle, etc.  I remember the post, it was in that whole section of &quot;The Arch-Mage Answers&quot; or something like that.  Higher wis does reduce your chance to fizzle I remember (though empiracally I think the difference between 175 and 200 is probably irrelevant... my ranger friend with 130 wis fizzles a lot more, though her spell skills aren't maxxed either, so not sure).  I'm not sure if it helps with other stuff.<br>
<br>
In regards to whether mana pool really matters I think of it this way...<br>
<br>
If you are doing a very safe camp with no surprises and everyone plays perfectly, mana pool is irrelevent.... but... if you get trained, get an unexpected pop, a series of high level mobs (ie several Vets in a row in Kael, or several named in a row in disco2), one nuke or one heal can make a difference between an evac and success.<br>
<br>
We've been in Karnors before, and we got a train of 8 (yes 8 though luckily in 2 waves) mobs.  I strongly feel that because of the mana pool of the cleric, enchanter, and druid, we were able to kill all 8 mobs (plus the 2 that were in camp).  (Granted we had a 55 bard too which helped a lot, but it went something like: we're all around 80 mana, train hits, druid and enc are doing respective crowd control, cleric is healing -- we're all dropping mana quickly, we're down to OOM by the time things are under control (ie all mezzed, rooted, or being tanked), bard is doing double mana to help us recover mana fast when something breaks.)<br>
<br>
In a raid situation, of course the appropriate resist is more important, but you want to have the most mana you can have of course, since you aren't going to be &quot;stabalizing&quot; your mana and being mana efficient.<br>
<br>
Just my 2cp<br>
<br>
- Xylem, E'ci <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showMessageRange?topicID=3169.topic&start=21&stop=23>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showMessage?topicID=3286.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showMessage?topicID=3350.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.emailToFriend?topicID=3169.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.threadControl?topicID=3169.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3169.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3169.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thedruidsgrovegeneral">General - EQ<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm27">General - DAOC<option value="thedruidsgrovegeneralot">General - OT<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm18">FAQ & Index<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm20">Spoilers<option value="thedruidsgrovespells">Spells<option valu